  "title": "Director of Administration",
  "description": "<h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Provide strategic and operational leadership across administration, facilities, HR administration, and internal controls.</p></li><li><p>Ensure full compliance with <strong>SSG / EduTrust</strong> and relevant Singapore regulatory requirements.</p></li><li><p>Oversee administrative operations, policies, processes, and continuous improvement initiatives.</p></li><li><p>Lead and develop administrative teams, fostering a professional and service-oriented culture.</p></li><li><p>Manage facilities, vendors, and resources to support academic and business operations.</p></li><li><p>Partner with senior management on budgeting, planning, and institutional growth initiatives.</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, Management, or a related field.</p></li><li><p><strong>8–12 years</strong> of relevant experience, with at least <strong>3–5 years in a senior leadership role</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge of <strong>Singapore College regulations, SSG/EduTrust frameworks</strong>, and employment laws.</p></li><li><p>Proven leadership, stakeholder management, and problem-solving skills.</p></li><li><p>Highly organised, detail-oriented, and able to manage multiple priorities.</p></li></ul>",
